19/04/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Court issued a one-month detention measure Wednesday (April 18th) for two war crimes suspects, arrested by the State Investigation and Protection Agency earlier this week.
Senad Dautovic, 47, and Enes Handzic, 44, former Bosniak police and military officers, are charged with committing atrocities against Bosnian Croats in Bugojno from 1992 to 1994.
(PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, Fena - 18/04/07)
